<P>Mean time, it is now ea&s;y, as you will ob&s;erve, to gue&s;s from what quarter the report I mention'd to you in one of my former came, That the younger &s;i&s;ter has robb'd the elder of her lover: For Betty whi&s;per'd it, at the time &s;he whi&s;per'd the re&s;t, that neither Lovelace nor you had done honourably by <HI>her</HI> young mi&s;tre&s;s.&mdash;How cruel, my dear, in you, to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ob the poor Bella of the only lover &s;he ever had!&mdash;At the in&s;tant too that &s;he was priding her&s;elf, that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ow, at la&s;t, &s;he &s;hould have it in her power not only <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o gratify her own &s;u&s;ceptibilities, but to give an ex|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">mple to the <HI>flirts</HI> of her &s;ex (my wor&s;hip's &s;elf the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rincipal, I &s;uppo&s;e, with her) how to govern their man with a &s;ilken rein, and without a kerb-bridle!</P>
