<P>But this was not enough to daunt him: The m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> is a very confident, he is a very bold, &s;taring man!&mdash;Indeed, my dear, the man is very confident.</P>
<P>He took the removed chair, and drew it &s;o ne<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> mine, &s;quatting in it with his ugly weight, that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> pre&s;s'd upon my hoop.&mdash;I was &s;o offended (all I h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> heard, as I &s;aid, in my head), that I removed to a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> other chair. I own I had too little command of m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">+&s;elf: It gave my brother and &s;i&s;ter too much adva<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">+tage; I dare &s;ay they took it:&mdash;But I did it involu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">+tarily, I think: I could not help it.&mdash;I knew n<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> what I did.</P>
